Class TurnsManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.TurnsManager
  • public class TurnsManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents the turns handler and is in charge of the logic of the problem. For more details about the context of the problem and the problem itself, got to: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1B5HBI3Hz4JossDKzX5d2sSnTj3zOvktyk7KiiJ_dFsY/edit
    Author:
    Sebastián García Acosta

    • Method Detail

      • addUser

        public void addUser​(java.lang.String n,
                    java.lang.String id,
                    java.lang.String tod,
                    java.lang.String cpn,
                    java.lang.String a,
                    Turn t)
             throws UserAlreadyRegisteredException,
                    BlankRequiredFieldException,
                    InvalidInputException
        Adds a user to the turns manager if and only if potential user's fields meet the following rules:
        Parameters:
        n - , String, name. REQUIRED FIELD. Must be alphabetic.
        id - , String id. REQUIRED FIELD. Must be numerical.
        tod - , String, type of document. REQUIRED FIELD. Possible values: CC, CE, PA, TI, RC (see User class for detailed explanation).
        cpn - , String cell-phone number. Must be numerical.
        a - , String, address. Optional field.
        t - , Turn, turn assigned to user. Initially is null. All parameters (n, id, cpn, a, t) are not null. post: User was added successfully if all required fields were not blank, all fields were in their corresponding format, and its id was unique. Otherwise, the corresponding exception was thrown.
        Throws:
        UserAlreadyRegisteredException - if another user with same id is found.
        BlankRequiredFieldException - if one of the REQUIRED FIELDS indicated is blank.
        InvalidInputException - if one of the numeric fields indicated above as numerical does not contain only numbers.

      • registerTurn

        public void registerTurn​(java.lang.String id)
                  throws UserAlreadyHasATurnException,
                         UserNotFoundException
        Registers next available turn to user with id specified.
        Parameters:
        id - , String, identification number of user to whom the turn will be assigned. Cannot be null. post: turn was registered successfully if parameter was not null, user was found and didn't have a turn assigned already; otherwise, corresponding exception was thrown. After setting turn to user, lasTurn was updated.
        Throws:
        UserNotFoundException - if user with the specified id is not found.
        UserAlreadyHasATurnException

      • generateNextTurnId

        public java.lang.String generateNextTurnId​(Turn currentTurn)
        Generates next turn id ranging from A00 to Z99.
        Parameters:
        currentTurn - , Turn, previous turn, based on this the next turn will be generated. E.g. if currentTurn was A0, next turn will be A1; if currentTurn was Z99, next turn will be A00.
        Returns:
        String, id of the next turn. Its first character is a letter and the rest are numbers.

      • dispatchTurn

        public void dispatchTurn​(java.lang.String state)
                  throws java.util.NoSuchElementException
        Dispatches the current turn: sets the state of current turn to either ATTENDED or USER_NOT_PRESENT.
        Parameters:
        state - , String, possible values are: "Attended." or "User not present". post: After update the state of the current turn, user that had that turn could register another turn. (User's field Turn will be set to null).
        Throws:
        java.util.NoSuchElementException
